# tests/integration/.gitignore
#
# The repo-root .gitignore blanket-ignores "*.xml" (it's there to
# squelch IS work-dir / coverage detritus). That accidentally hides
# the Maven pom.xml under restassured/, so we re-include it.
#
# Re-include rules only work when the parent directory is itself NOT
# ignored. tests/integration/ is not ignored anywhere, so the
# negations below lift these files out of the global ignore.

!restassured/pom.xml

# --- Maven build output --------------------------------------------
restassured/target/

# --- Per-developer convenience artifacts ---------------------------
# Newman/k6 are usually invoked through scripts/test-integration.sh
# which writes to <repo>/reports/integration/, but if a developer
# runs them directly inside tests/integration/, ignore the spillover.
*.har
report.html
summary.json
